gomodel:SYNGO_5147  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1, 2, 3: RIL (PDLIM4) interacts with AMPA receptors (GRIA1, 2/3) and α-actinin (ACTN1 and ACTN2).\n\nFigure 7, 8: RIL (PDLIM4) overexpression increased the abundance of GRIA1-containing receptors in dendritic spines and enhanced AMPA receptor-mediated synaptic currents in hippocampal primary neurons.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Hippocampal primary cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 Sprague Dawley tissue\"\n\n\"Generation of anti-RIL antibody. Anti-RIL polyclonal serum against the C-terminal RIL aa 317-330 peptide CDVVAVYPNAKVEL was generated at AnaSpec (San Jose, CA). Affinity purification was done by peptide-coupled SulfoLink gel (Pierce,Rockford, IL) column: 20 ml of serum, diluted 1:10 in 4°C cold PBS, was run over the column overnight at 4°C. After wash with PBS, 1 ml fractions were eluted with glycine, pH 2.5, and immediately neutralized with 1/10 volume of 1 m Tris, pH 8.0. Anti-RIL antibody (Ab)-positive fractions were selected by Western blotting of FlagRIL-expressing African green monkey kidney fibroblast cells (COS)1 lysate.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5147" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

